---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Policy"
  description="Our commitment to accuracy, transparency, and editorial independence in peptide research coverage."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <header class="mb-12 relative">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-[var(--primary)]/10 via-transparent to-transparent rounded-2xl -z-10"></div>
      <div class="p-6">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white">Editorial Policy</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-xl text-white/80">
          Our commitment to accuracy, transparency, and editorial independence.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2>Editorial Independence</h2>
      <p>
        Our editorial content is produced independently of any commercial relationships.
        Sponsors and partners have no influence over:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Which peptides we cover</li>
        <li>How we grade evidence</li>
        <li>What conclusions we draw from research</li>
        <li>Our editorial priorities or publishing schedule</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Accuracy Standards</h2>
      <p>We maintain accuracy through:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Citation verification</strong> — Every cited source is verified to exist and
          accurately represent the claim
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Automated checks</strong> — Our publishing system validates that all cited
          PMIDs, DOIs, and trial IDs exist
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Human review</strong> — All content passes editorial review before publication
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Open corrections</strong> — We promptly correct errors and note corrections
          transparently
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Content Guidelines</h2>
      <h3>What We Include</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Peer-reviewed research findings</li>
        <li>Clinical trial data and regulatory information</li>
        <li>Mechanistic explanations from established science</li>
        <li>Safety signals and adverse event reports</li>
        <li>Clearly labeled inferences with confidence levels</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>What We Exclude</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Dosing protocols or administration instructions</li>
        <li>Sourcing, purchasing, or vendor information</li>
        <li>Personal medical advice or recommendations</li>
        <li>Unsubstantiated claims or anecdotal evidence presented as fact</li>
        <li>Content that could facilitate misuse</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Language & Tone</h2>
      <p>
        We write for an educated general audience. Our content is:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Neutral</strong> — No promotional language or hype</li>
        <li><strong>Precise</strong> — Clear about what evidence shows and doesn't show</li>
        <li><strong>Accessible</strong> — Technical terms are explained; jargon is minimized</li>
        <li><strong>Honest</strong> — We acknowledge uncertainty and limitations</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Corrections Policy</h2>
      <p>
        When we make errors, we correct them transparently:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Minor corrections (typos, formatting) are made without notation</li>
        <li>Substantive corrections are noted at the bottom of the affected page</li>
        <li>Significant errors affecting conclusions trigger a prominent correction notice</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Conflicts of Interest</h2>
      <p>
        We disclose any relevant conflicts of interest. Our team members do not:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Hold financial interests in peptide manufacturers or distributors</li>
        <li>Accept payment from sources we cover for favorable coverage</li>
        <li>Allow sponsors to review or approve editorial content before publication</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-white/70">
        Last updated: January 2026
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
